        "title": "How to check the nested objects are equal or not in Junit5",
        "body": "<p>When a method returns a nested object as a response than how can we test that method?\nI am writing the code in java 8 and junit5.\nI have POJOs like below<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>Class Phone{\n  int id;\n  String name;\n}\nClass Address{\nString street;\nString city;\n}\nClass Person {\n List&lt;Phone&gt; phones;\n Address address;\n String name;\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>I have a method like below<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>public Person getPerson(String name){\nreturn persons.stream().filter(person -&gt; person.getName().equals(name)).findAny().orElse(null);\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Here, How can I test this method with junit5?<\/p>\n",
