        "body": "<p>I would recommend you to user the <a href=\"http://junit.sourceforge.net/javadoc/org/junit/Assert.html\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">assertEquals()<\/a> method in JUnit. Note that, as you can see in the <a href=\"https://github.com/junit-team/junit4/blob/master/src/main/java/junit/framework/Assert.java\" rel=\"nofollow noreferrer\">code<\/a> of the method, it uses the .equals() method. <\/p>\n\n<p>So, in order for it to work, you should override the equals method in each of the classes whose objects you are trying to test/compare.<\/p>\n",
